my ad set is doing poorly after completing the learning phase, how can I adjust

If your ad set is performing poorly after completing the learning phase, here are a few steps you can take to adjust:

1. **Review Your CPA**: If your actual CPA is higher than expected, consider adjusting your budget or targeting.

2. **Adjust Budget Gradually**: Increase or decrease the budget by a maximum of 30-50% each time and monitor performance for 2-3 days to gauge the impact.

3. **Optimize Ad Sets**: Keep the higher-performing ad sets active and consider pausing those that aren't performing well.

4. **Test New Creatives**: Sometimes refreshing your creative content can help improve engagement and performance.

5. **Re-evaluate Targeting**: Ensure that your targeting aligns with your audience's demographics and interests.

For more detailed guidance, you can check out our best practices article [here](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/23055076590221-Maximize-Conversions-Best-Practices). Let me know if there's anything else I can help with!

Can tCPA significantly increase a budget?

Yes, using tCPA (Target Cost Per Acquisition) can help optimize your budget by focusing on acquiring conversions at a target cost. However, it's important to increase your daily budget gradually, about 20-30% every 2-3 days, to maintain performance stability. You can also use the bid estimation tool to identify ad sets with high growth potential and project conversion metrics based on bid rate increases. For more details, you can check out our best practices here: [tCPA Best Practices](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/18020232662797-tCPA-Best-Practices).
